00:16:42,634 --> 00:16:45,330
我那時以為他只是和我耍脾氣
I thought he'd simply walked out on me.

178
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:50,464
然後有名醫生...今晚找上我
Then a... doctor contacted me this evening.

179
00:16:50,509 --> 00:16:52,136
你們結婚多久了?
How long have you been married?

180
00:16:52,177 --> 00:16:53,474
快4年了
Nearly four years.

181
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:56,445
為什麼這麼問?
Why do you ask?

182
00:16:56,482 --> 00:16:59,500
因為你似乎並不喜歡戴著戒指
Because you seem uncomfortable with your ring.

183
00:16:59,618 --> 00:17:03,281
好像戴著很不習慣
As if you were... unaccustomed to wearing it.

184
00:17:03,322 --> 00:17:04,755
不 我從不把它摘下來
No, I never take it off.

185
00:17:11,330 --> 00:17:14,757
你認識這些人嗎?
Do these names mean anything to you?

186
00:17:20,706 --> 00:17:22,606
不 她們是誰
No. Who are these women?

187
00:17:23,509 --> 00:17:25,204
你們為什麼要找我丈夫
Why are you looking for my husband?

188
00:17:25,911 --> 00:17:27,776
他犯了什麼罪?
Are you going to accuse him of something?

189
00:17:27,813 --> 00:17:30,111
他涉嫌謀殺
Maybe. Maybe murder.

190
00:17:30,149 --> 00:17:31,173
殺了誰?
Whose murder?

191
00:17:32,584 --> 00:17:36,281
哪一個?      全部
- Which one?      - All of them.

192
00:17:37,256 --> 00:17:39,451
默多剋夫人 對不起 我很抱歉
Mrs. Murdoch, I am sorry, I'm sorry.

193
00:17:39,491 --> 00:17:40,549
我無意嚇你
I didn't mean to alarm you.

194
00:17:40,592 --> 00:17:43,152
我不該來這 你我都錯了
I'm so sorry that I came. Just both made a mistake.

195
00:17:43,195 --> 00:17:44,662
默多剋夫人  如果你不介意
Mrs. Murdoch, if you please.

196
00:17:44,696 --> 00:17:47,130
請給我點時間解釋...
If you'll just give me half a second to explain...

197
00:17:50,469 --> 00:17:51,458
我一會就回來
I'll be right out.

198
00:18:15,627 --> 00:18:17,925
我們見過面嗎?
Have we met before?

199
00:18:18,563 --> 00:18:21,592
如果有 希望你還活著
If we did... I hope you're still breathing.

200
00:18:21,633 --> 00:18:23,260
甜心 你叫什麼名字?
What's your name, honey?

201
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:26,302
約翰
John.

202
00:18:27,039 --> 00:18:28,802
嗯 我的顧客都能自稱約翰
Well, that's an appropriate name.

203
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:30,697
是
Yeah.

204
00:18:36,849 --> 00:18:38,043
我在想
I was just thinking.

205
00:18:42,254 --> 00:18:43,812
你為什麼幹這一行...
What you do...

206
00:18:45,057 --> 00:18:48,356
有點危險...
seems kind of dangerous...

207
00:18:48,693 --> 00:18:50,384
例如現在
right now.

208
00:18:50,429 --> 00:18:52,158
我的意思是 你怎知我不是殺手?
I mean, how do you know I'm not the killer?

209
00:18:52,197 --> 00:18:55,394
你看上去不像? 為什麼這麼問
You don't seem like the killer type. Why?

210
00:18:56,602 --> 00:18:59,127
難道你有什麼特別需要嗎?
You feeling any urges I should know about?

211
00:19:20,659 --> 00:19:22,251
啊 真可惡
Aw, shoot.

212
00:20:20,919 --> 00:20:24,650
似乎你已發現了你的惡劣本性
So it seems you've discovered your unpleasant nature.

213
00:20:27,826 --> 00:20:28,850
你們是誰?
Who are you?

214
00:20:28,894 --> 00:20:32,557
我們也有此問 是吧?
We might ask the same question, yes?

215
00:20:32,598 --> 00:20:35,192
沉睡吧
Sleep now.

216
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:02,892
他懂得調諧
He can tune.

217
00:21:55,981 --> 00:21:59,280
該怎麼辦? 此人是危險人物
What is to be done? This man is dangerous.

218
00:21:59,318 --> 00:22:01,252
聽說他也會調諧之術
It is said he is able to tune.

219
00:22:01,286 --> 00:22:02,651
不可能
Impossible.

220
00:22:02,688 --> 00:22:05,486
我們親眼所見
We have seen it with our own eyes.

221
00:22:05,524 --> 00:22:07,958
一般人如果沒有注射
On occasion the imprinting does not take.

222
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:10,962
醒來後就會舉止失常
They behave erratically when they awaken.

223
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:14,625
像迷失的孩童一樣四處遊蕩
We find them wandering like lost children.

224
00:22:14,666 --> 00:22:16,827
但這個人不同 是嗎?
But this one was different, yes?

225
00:22:16,868 --> 00:22:18,563
醫生怎麼說?
What has the doctor to say about this?

226
00:22:18,603 --> 00:22:20,594
他還沒報告
He has failed to report in.

227
00:22:20,639 --> 00:22:23,767
快先生呢?      快先生不在了
- And Mr. Quick?      - No more Mr. Quick.

228
00:22:23,809 --> 00:22:26,801
他已經死了
Mr. Quick, dead, yes.

229
00:22:29,848 --> 00:22:32,442
可憐的快先生
Poor, poor Mr. Quick.

230
00:22:32,484 --> 00:22:35,351
書先生知道嗎
Mr. Book, does he know?

231
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:38,519
我們不該知道嗎 手先生?
Should we not know, Mr. Hand?

232
00:22:39,491 --> 00:22:42,358
我們本想獲得更多訊息後再告訴你們
We had hoped to learn more before sharing with you.

233
00:22:42,394 --> 00:22:45,329
在抓到他之前我們什麼都不會知道
We can know nothing until we possess him.

234
00:22:46,398 --> 00:22:48,958
夜先生 你負責搜索東方
Mr. Night, you will take the East.

235
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:51,798
面先生 你負責搜索西方
Mr. Face, you the West.

236
00:22:51,837 --> 00:22:53,930
套先生 你負責搜索南方
Mr. Glove, the South.

237
00:22:53,972 --> 00:22:56,202
影先生 你負責搜索北方
Mr. Shade, the North.

238
00:22:57,743 --> 00:23:00,712
我們必須抓到他
We must have this man.

239
00:23:14,359 --> 00:23:15,994
你真的認為
Do you really think

240
00:23:15,994 --> 00:23:19,353
我丈夫是連環殺人犯?
my husband could be capable of committing those murders?

241
00:23:19,931 --> 00:23:21,356
你呢?
Do you?

242
00:23:23,034 --> 00:23:26,092
希望是我判斷失誤吧
Let's hope, for both our sakes, that I'm wrong.

243
00:23:54,599 --> 00:23:55,861
約翰
John.

244
00:24:10,215 --> 00:24:12,342
我好擔心你
I've been so worried about you.

245
00:24:15,754 --> 00:24:17,847
你是在懲罰我嗎?
Are you punishing me?

246
00:24:17,889 --> 00:24:20,483
如果你用失蹤來懲罰我
You know, if disappearing is your way of punishing me...

247
00:24:20,525 --> 00:24:21,617
那我不喜歡
I don't appreciate it.

248
00:24:21,660 --> 00:24:23,719
我不知道你在說什麼
I don't know what you're talking about.

249
00:24:26,565 --> 00:24:29,056
我在口袋裡找到這些鑰匙
I found these keys in my pocket...

250
00:24:29,100 --> 00:24:31,796
於是我想我住在這裡
so I assume I live here.

251
00:24:31,837 --> 00:24:33,600
你應該是我妻子吧?
You supposed to be my wife?

252
00:24:33,638 --> 00:24:35,663
應該是?
Supposed to be?

253
00:24:35,707 --> 00:24:37,732
約翰
John.

254
00:24:38,243 --> 00:24:40,006
難道你真的...
You really...

255
00:24:40,045 --> 00:24:42,546
不知道我是誰?
don't know who I am, do you?

256
00:24:43,315 --> 00:24:44,509
你的醫生找過我
Your doctor called me.

257
00:24:44,549 --> 00:24:46,039
這正是他擔心的
He was worried that this might happen.

258
00:24:46,084 --> 00:24:47,574
我的醫生?
My doctor?

259
00:24:47,619 --> 00:24:50,144
是的 他...
Yeah. He...

260
00:24:50,188 --> 00:24:52,213
給了我他的名片
he gave me his card.

261
00:24:52,257 --> 00:24:54,782
他急著找你
He's desperate to find you.

262
00:24:54,826 --> 00:24:57,351
施列伯
Schreber.

263
00:25:01,666 --> 00:25:03,759
我覺得自己活在別人的噩夢裡
I feel like I'm living out someone else's nightmare.

264
00:25:03,802 --> 00:25:06,566
我到底怎麼了 為什麼我要去看醫生?
What happened to me? Why was I seeing a doctor?

265
00:25:07,305 --> 00:25:09,432
因為我有外遇
I had an affair.

266
00:25:10,509 --> 00:25:12,943
你很生我的氣
You were angry at me.

267
00:25:15,380 --> 00:25:17,245
警察在找你
The police are looking for you.

268
00:25:17,282 --> 00:25:19,580
我知道 我有看報紙
I know. I saw the papers.

269
00:25:19,618 --> 00:25:22,178
"妓女殺手逍遙法外"
"Killer stalks city streetwalkers."

270
00:25:25,690 --> 00:25:28,385
我和其中一名受害者在一起
I was with one of those women...

271
00:25:29,327 --> 00:25:31,124
就在昨晚
before I came here tonight.

272
00:25:31,796 --> 00:25:33,457
我不明白
I don't understand.

273
00:25:33,498 --> 00:25:34,965
我在自助餐廳外遇見她
I met her outside an Automat.

274
00:25:36,468 --> 00:25:39,028
我也許是想試一下自己
I guess I wanted to test myself.

275
00:25:39,070 --> 00:25:43,006
我想知道我是不是殺人犯
I wanted to know if I had it in me to do those things.

276
00:25:43,041 --> 00:25:45,409
我也許是瘋了 但不管怎樣
Maybe I have lost my mind, but whoever I am,

277
00:25:45,409 --> 00:25:47,637
我還是我 不是殺人犯
I'm still me and I'm not a killer.

278
00:25:53,985 --> 00:25:55,453
我相信你
I believe you.

279
00:25:56,855 --> 00:25:58,316
真的嗎?
You do?

280
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:03,216
那是什麼?
What?

281
00:26:03,261 --> 00:26:06,059
外面那輛車 你回來坐的那輛
The car outside, the one you arrived in.

282
00:26:06,097 --> 00:26:08,429
是警察 他送我回來的
It's a cop. He dropped me off here.

283
00:26:10,569 --> 00:26:13,197
我不知道他還沒走
I didn't know he was still here.

284
00:26:13,238 --> 00:26:14,262
約翰
John.

285
00:26:15,574 --> 00:26:17,804
站那別動!
Hold it right there, mister!

286
00:26:19,711 --> 00:26:21,679
等下 你抓錯人了
Wait. You have the wrong man.

287
00:26:21,713 --> 00:26:22,839
請站到旁邊 好嗎?
Stand aside, will you, please?

288
00:26:22,881 --> 00:26:24,473
我沒殺人
I didn't kill anyone.

289
00:26:24,516 --> 00:26:27,610
你現在只是嫌疑犯 跟我走
Right now what you are is a suspect. Turn yourself in.

290
00:26:28,553 --> 00:26:30,111
我會聽你解釋
I'll listen to whatever you have to say.

291
00:26:30,155 --> 00:26:32,055
你不會相信我要說的話的
You're not gonna believe what I have to say.

292
00:26:33,158 --> 00:26:34,250
說說看
Try me.

293
00:26:34,859 --> 00:26:36,417
有人在追我
There's someone after me.

294
00:26:36,461 --> 00:26:39,589
一夥人 他們要我死
There's this group of men. They want me dead.

295
00:26:39,631 --> 00:26:42,259
而且我不知道是否...他們甚至不是...
And I don't even know if... They're not even...

296
00:26:43,034 --> 00:26:45,264
好吧 誰會聽個瘋子說話
Yeah, who's gonna listen to a madman?

297
00:26:45,303 --> 00:26:47,100
請站到旁邊 默多剋夫人
Stand aside, Mrs. Murdoch.

298
00:26:47,138 --> 00:26:48,264
快逃!
Run!

299
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:54,840
怎麼就沒人聽我的
No one ever listens to me.

300
00:27:00,385 --> 00:27:01,511
默多克 站住!
Murdoch, stop!

301
00:27:06,591 --> 00:27:07,456
默多克!
Murdoch!

302
00:27:44,262 --> 00:27:45,298
還有多遠
How much further?

303
00:27:45,298 --> 00:27:46,720
就快到了 夥計
We're almost there, buddy.

304
00:27:49,434 --> 00:27:52,633
你知道怎麼去貝殼海灘嗎
Hey, you happen to know the way to Shell Beach?

305
00:27:52,771 --> 00:27:53,672
我怎麼會不知道
You're kidding.

306
00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:55,672
我和老婆就是在那度蜜月的
Me and the missus spent our honeymoon there.

307
00:27:55,707 --> 00:27:58,437
只要你走主街西路...
All you gotta do is take Main Street west to...

308
00:28:01,279 --> 00:28:02,974
還是要走跨...
Or is it the cross...

309
00:28:03,500 --> 00:28:06,643
好奇怪 我好像記不清
You know, that's funny. I can't seem to remember...

310
00:28:06,685 --> 00:28:08,983
該走主街西路還是跨鎮大道
if it's Main Street west or the cross-town.

311
00:28:13,658 --> 00:28:17,185
對不起 探長 我很樂意協助你破案
I'm sorry, Inspector, I cannot be of more assistance...

312
00:28:17,228 --> 00:28:19,093
但我和人有約 快遲到了
but I am running late for an appointment.

313
00:28:19,130 --> 00:28:21,325
感謝你抽空來幫忙
Well, I appreciate your taking the time.

314
00:28:29,641 --> 00:28:31,939
有件事我仍然困惑不解
There's just one thing that puzzles me.

315
00:28:31,976 --> 00:28:36,640
我辦案生涯中見過不少殺人犯
I've met quite a few murderers in the course of my work.

316
00:28:36,681 --> 00:28:39,343
但默多克不像是殺人犯
Murdoch doesn't strike me as one.

317
00:28:39,384 --> 00:28:42,647
也許你還沒去深入瞭解
Perhaps you are not accustomed to digging deep enough.

318
00:28:42,647 --> 00:28:45,613
沒人能騙得過我 醫生
Well, I do know when someone is lying to me, Doctor.

319
00:28:45,657 --> 00:28:48,285
恕我冒昧 探長 你不是心理醫生
Forgive me, Inspector, but you are not a clinician.

320
00:28:48,526 --> 00:28:52,057
判斷人性恰好是我的工作
Judging personalities happens to be my business.

321
00:28:52,097 --> 00:28:54,122
你能否為我提供些建議?
Well, maybe you could give me a few pointers.

322
00:28:54,165 --> 00:28:55,896
當然
Certainly.

323
00:28:56,034 --> 00:28:58,059
以你為例
Let's take you, for instance.

324
00:28:58,103 --> 00:29:01,470
你是個挑剔的人 喜歡追根究底
You are a fastidious man, driven.

325
00:29:01,506 --> 00:29:03,565
注重細節
Consumed by details.

326
00:29:04,342 --> 00:29:06,242
你的生活
I would say your life is...

327
00:29:07,545 --> 00:29:08,534
很孤獨
rather Ionely.

328
00:29:09,347 --> 00:29:11,907
晚安 探長 我真的得走了
Good evening, Inspector. I really must be going.

329
00:29:53,291 --> 00:29:57,625
泳池即將關閉
Closing time. The pool is now closed.

330
00:30:04,402 --> 00:30:05,391
施列伯醫生
Dr. Schreber.

331
00:30:07,172 --> 00:30:09,169
真是不幸
Most unfortunate it is

332
00:30:09,170 --> 00:30:11,801
要我們親自來找你
that we were forced to seek you out here.

333
00:30:12,744 --> 00:30:15,406
你知道我們是多麼討厭
You know how uncomfortable we find all this...

334
00:30:16,114 --> 00:30:17,376
濕氣
moisture.

335
00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:20,979
對不起 我...      沒有報告 是的
- I'm sorry. I...      - Failed to report in, yes.

336
00:30:21,019 --> 00:30:23,647
我當時被嚇到了 我的心臟很脆弱
I was frightened. I have a weak heart, you know.

337
00:30:23,688 --> 00:30:27,556
我們認為 你脆弱的不是心臟
Your weakness is not, we think, an affair of the heart.

338
00:30:27,592 --> 00:30:30,254
我們在他的旅館房間裡找到這個
We found this in his hotel room.

339
00:30:30,295 --> 00:30:34,231
我們是不是要再給默多克灌輸記憶?
Must we reproduce Mr. Murdoch's memories again?

340
00:30:34,265 --> 00:30:35,323
我試著給他注射
I tried to imprint him...

341
00:30:35,366 --> 00:30:37,493
但他醒了 把注射器給打碎了
but he woke up, he knocked the syringe right out of my hand.

342
00:30:37,535 --> 00:30:39,628
我要阻止他 但他太快了
I tried to stop him but he was too fast.

343
00:30:39,671 --> 00:30:40,831
然後他失憶了?
He has no memories, then?

344
00:30:40,872 --> 00:30:44,239
只有記憶碎片 因為程序被中斷了
Only fragments. The procedure, it was interrupted.

345
00:30:44,275 --> 00:30:47,478
我想只要再抓到他就行了
I guess it's only a matter of rounding him up.

346
00:30:47,812 --> 00:30:49,670
以前也抓過逃脫者 不是嗎?
You have had strays before, right?

347
00:30:49,714 --> 00:30:53,343
這個人不一樣 醫生 他會調諧
This is no stray, Doctor. This one can tune.

348
00:30:53,785 --> 00:30:56,583
不可能 調諧只有你們會
But that's impossible. I thought only you had that ability.

349
00:30:56,621 --> 00:30:57,621
你會重新
You will process

350
00:30:57,621 --> 00:31:00,921
給他灌輸另一種模板記憶吧?
another template of the subject's memories, yes?

351
00:31:00,959 --> 00:31:02,688
當然 我會再給他注射
Of course. I'll imprint him again.

352
00:31:02,727 --> 00:31:07,221
不 這次我們另有目的
No. We require them for a quite different purpose.

353
00:31:08,066 --> 00:31:10,534
快午夜了 施列伯醫生
It's almost midnight, Dr. Schreber.

354
00:31:10,568 --> 00:31:13,002
今晚調諧之後 我們再找你談話 不過...
We'll talk again after tonight's tuning, but...

355
00:31:13,571 --> 00:31:15,368
別再推遲 好嗎?
no more delays, yes?

356
00:31:15,406 --> 00:31:20,207
你得絕對的服從
No more inconsistencies in your behavior.

357
00:31:27,719 --> 00:31:30,586
你看上去很虛弱 醫生
You appear quite frail, Doctor.

358
00:31:31,356 --> 00:31:34,848
該多鍛煉鍛煉
Perhaps some exercise would do you good.

